text.text:
BEST Guinness and cocktails in town!
The best way to attack naga house for the most wonderful evening is to grab a couple of friends, order some Guinness and try their unique cocktails that are super affordable! Plenty of delicious food to pick from. After a couple round of drinks, ask the friendly tatted bartenders for off menu special or yummy cocktails like the Ramos Gin fizz, espresso martini twist!

Lovely place to spend the evening and the atmosphere was lively yet chill for small groups.

We got their tater tots and drinks. The drinks were nice and the tater tots were absolutely AMAZING üî• Crispy, flavourful and decent portion! They had mains as well, but we didn't get the chance to try them.

The staff and service was good as well. Overall, would recommend.

text.text:
Great service and even better food. Celebrated my husband's 29th birthday here and it was the best decision made because he and I loved the food so much. We ordered the Ramen Risotto, the BBQ Bacon Smashed Burger and Tater Tots. All were very good.

The sour plum shots were unexpectedly refreshing and some Thai Milk Tea ice cream to end the meal. I don't usually eat ice cream after meals but this was an exception because it was so good. Only downside was that the new menu provided on google is not updated, but with a bit of searching, it's available to view on Quandoo.

Great experience & will definitely come back again to try out other things on the menu.
